<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Redescribed ♂ (RMNH) from Germany (Graswang). Length of fore wing 6.2 mm, of body 8.0 mm. Entire body with long whitish setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head.</emphasis>
Antennal segments of ♂ 60, length of antenna 1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
fore wing, its subapical segments somewhat longer than wide; frons medially largely smooth, laterally with some fine curved rugae; OOL 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of posterior ocellus, and punctate-rugose, POL approx. half as long as diameter of ocellus; vertex spaced rugose, shiny; clypeus punctate; ventral margin of clypeus rather thick but distinctly protruding forwards (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 411–424" captionStartId="F62" captionText="Figures 411 - 424. Aleiodes hirtus (Thomson), ♀, Scotland, Peebles 411 fore wing 412 hind wing 413 mesosoma lateral 414 mesosoma dorsal 415 metasoma dorsal 416 fore femur lateral 417 hind femur lateral 418 antenna 419 head anterior 420 head dorsal 421 head lateral 422 base of antenna 423 apex of antenna 424 inner hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.919.39642.figures411-424" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/390106" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">421</figureCitation>
); width of hypoclypeal depression 0.55 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
minimum width of face (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 411–424" captionStartId="F62" captionText="Figures 411 - 424. Aleiodes hirtus (Thomson), ♀, Scotland, Peebles 411 fore wing 412 hind wing 413 mesosoma lateral 414 mesosoma dorsal 415 metasoma dorsal 416 fore femur lateral 417 hind femur lateral 418 antenna 419 head anterior 420 head dorsal 421 head lateral 422 base of antenna 423 apex of antenna 424 inner hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.919.39642.figures411-424" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/390106" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">419</figureCitation>
); length of eye 1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
temple in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 411–424" captionStartId="F62" captionText="Figures 411 - 424. Aleiodes hirtus (Thomson), ♀, Scotland, Peebles 411 fore wing 412 hind wing 413 mesosoma lateral 414 mesosoma dorsal 415 metasoma dorsal 416 fore femur lateral 417 hind femur lateral 418 antenna 419 head anterior 420 head dorsal 421 head lateral 422 base of antenna 423 apex of antenna 424 inner hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.919.39642.figures411-424" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/390106" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">420</figureCitation>
), temples conspicuously setose (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 411–424" captionStartId="F62" captionText="Figures 411 - 424. Aleiodes hirtus (Thomson), ♀, Scotland, Peebles 411 fore wing 412 hind wing 413 mesosoma lateral 414 mesosoma dorsal 415 metasoma dorsal 416 fore femur lateral 417 hind femur lateral 418 antenna 419 head anterior 420 head dorsal 421 head lateral 422 base of antenna 423 apex of antenna 424 inner hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.919.39642.figures411-424" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/390106" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">419</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 425–427" captionStartId="F63" captionText="Figures 425 - 427. Aleiodes hirtus (Thomson), ♂, England, Chippenham Fen 425 habitus lateral 426 head and anterior part of mesosoma lateral 427 propodeum and 1 st - 3 rd metasomal segments lateral." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.919.39642.figures425-427" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/390107" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">426</figureCitation>
); vertex behind stemmaticum rugose; clypeus near lower level of eyes; length of malar space 0.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of eye in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum rugose and anteriorly oblique, without antescutal depression; mesoscutal lobes large smooth and shiny, only indistinctly punctulate and densely setose; precoxal area of mesopleuron punctulate and medially with some superficial rugulae; remainder of mesopleuron sparsely punctate; scutellum sparsely punctate and largely smooth, posteriorly with lateral rugae; propodeum rather convex and coarsely rugose, its medio-longitudinal carina only in anterior half of propodeum.
</paragraph>
